17 13:03:14','2012-05-17 13:03:14','',1,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=47',0,'revision','',0),(48,1,'2012-07-09 19:34:45','2012-07-09 18:34:45','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','inherit','open','open','','1-autosave','','','2012-07-09 19:34:45','2012-07-09 18:34:45','',1,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=48',0,'revision','',0),(52,1,'2012-04-22 19:48:35','2012-04-22 18:48:35','When you hang around anywhere, you start to pick up all kinds of things - new ways of doing things,what is important to that particular group and so on.\r\n\r\nHang around a church community and after not too long you will hear about people praying or even come across people actually doing so!\r\n\r\nReally? People with brains who believe that the God of the universe, whom they cannot see, actually listens! That prayer can actually make a difference!\r\n\r\nCan it? What do you think? Is there any evidence?\r\n\r\nI\'m not advocating clinical trials help on this subject necessarily. There have been a number of academic research papers written on prayer based on trials carried out. Overall it seems that there has been no clear cut conclusion that prayer makes a difference. This said, there are all kinds of other factors that come into play - including does God do prayer answers on tap for a test?\r\n\r\nAre there mysteries and challenges when it comes to the subject of prayer? Yes there are despite the easy formulas that some in the \'christian world\' would like to put forward about praying.\r\n\r\nYet I want to write here that I believe in prayer. Or more precisely I believe in the One I pray to! Christ said \'when you pray...\'  not if! The Bible also says based on realistic fact that all too often we do not know how to pray but... here comes some good news -  the Holy Spirit helps us (you can check that out in Romans 8 in the New Testament).\r\n\r\nPrayer of course is not just about asking..... it is about listening too. Perhaps in fact it is more about listening... Taking time to reflect, to allow Bible passages or other things to be used by God to speak into our lives. To allow our hearts to be examined. To be still... now there is a challenge very often! Turn off all the electronics, get rid of the noise so that we can hear the true signals that perhaps God wants to send our way through His word.\r\n\r\nChrist spoke about how human fathers, though doing things wrong at times, know how to good things to their children. Christ then said, \'how much will your Father in heaven give good gifts to those who ask him\' (Matthew\'s Gospel - chapter 7)\r\n\r\nDo we see God that way at all? Not that this means He is some kind of celestial fairy in the sky dishing out everything we want! But He has a heart towards people and He is a generous God.\r\n\r\n\'But what about.....?\' you might ask.  Yes there are plenty of things we might raise to protest against the idea God is generous or answers prayer. Yet the Bible does not duck this  - check out the Psalms for instance. All kinds of human experiences come up very honestly in prayers there.\r\n\r\nA book I would recommend is Phillip Yancey\'s book simply entitled \'Prayer\' - well worth reading.\r\n\r\nLastly I mention one last Bible verse as ICL has a Week of Prayer: \"without faith it is impossible to please God because anyone who comes to him must believe that he exists and that he rewards those who earnestly seek him\" (Hebrews 11:6, New Testament)\r\n\r\nIf you don\'t believe that he exists... well you are not going to pray anyway. But also if we don\'t believe that He will respond, we also will probably not pray...\r\n\r\nSo what will it be? Think about it and probably more importantly, why not pray too?\r\n\r\nAndy','Crazy to pray','','publish','open','open','','crazy-to-pray','','','2012-07-09 19:50:31','2012-07-09 18:50:31','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=52',0,'post','',0),(51,1,'2012-07-09 19:47:23','2012-07-09 18:47:23','<span